<h2>MPkn: Calculations of One Discrete Model in Several Time Steps</h2>
<p>A matrix discrete model having the form
    'M[i+1] = (I + Q)*M[i]'.
    The calculation of the values of 'M[i]' only for
    pre-selected values of 'i'. The method of calculation
    is presented in the vignette 'Fundament' ('Base'). Maybe it&lsquo;s own
    idea of the author of the package. A weakness is that the method
    gives information only in selected steps of the process.
    It mainly refers to cases with matrices that are not Markov chain.
    If &rsquo;Q' is Markov transition matrix, then MUPkL() may be
    used to calculate the steady-state distribution 'p' for
    'p = Q*p'.
    Matrix power of non integer (matrix.powerni()) gives
    the same results as a mpower() from package 'matlib'.
    References:
    "Markov chains",
    (&lt;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markov_chain#Expected_number_of_visits">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markov_chain#Expected_number_of_visits</a>&gt;).
    Donald R. Burleson, Ph.D. (2005), 
    "ON NON-INTEGER POWERS OF A SQUARE MATRIX", 
    (&lt;<a href="http://www.blackmesapress.com/Eigenvalues.htm">http://www.blackmesapress.com/Eigenvalues.htm</a>&gt;).</p>
